»CL0:           [Introduction]

Christmas time; a widely recognized
holiday season dedicated to
traditions and time spent with the
family. The demo scene also has
it's traditions, and christmas time
is particular holy: Going to The
Party.

For the 8th time in a row, we're 
proud to hold our annual party in
late December and feature more
competitions, prizes, events,
surprises, and activities than
ever. Experience the real party 
feeling, meet friends, and see the
master work of soon-to-be computer
and digital arts professionals. Or
stare at your monitor for 70 hours
straight, live on Coke and peanuts,
feel the true stress of meeting
deadlines, and watch Amiga demos at
04:30 in the morning without
knowing why. In any case, you'll
have to ask yourself:

- Do You Believe in Life After
Christmas? 







            [Where & When]

The Party 1998 will be held in
Messecenter Aars, like the previous
years. To avoid any power failures,
the entire powergrid has been
redesigned, and the conference
center is currently expanding, to
meet our space demands. The Party
1998 will be held from Sunday 27
December at 08:00 CET to Tuesday 29
December at 15:00 CET.








             [Facilities]

* Room for min. 3500 people!
* A seperate sleeping area
* Cafeteria and kiosk will be
  open 24h.
* Extremely powerful PA
  equipment and a 10x8 meter
  main screen
* Huge party network and fast
  internet link
* Live internet broadcast
* LaserDisc Room!
* Free access to bath & showers!
* The Party 1998 T-Shirts will 
 be sold




 [Events]

* 55 hours non-stop activities
* 16 main compos with great
  prizes
* Traditional party-events like
  Body-Crashing and DiskOs
* Fast Website Competition
* Rave in the Sleeping Hall
* Live concert on stage 
* Seminars and conferences
* Computer game championship 
* Plus much more...

 [Network]

10Mbit Twisted Pair for the people 
from a monster backbone, KICK-ASS 
FTP servers and Internet for
everyone. [Yawn -Cyt]
