               [Rules]

* If you want to take part in a
  competition you must be
  present at The Party during
  the presentation and prize
  ceremony.
* If too many contributions are
  delivered for a competition a
  jury will select contribution
  for presentation.
* Contributions can only
  participate in one
  competition.
* We will copy and spread all
  contributions.
* Contributions must be final,
  no bug-fixes will be accepted
  before or after presentation.
* Contributions must be uploade
  via network, or handed over i
  the information on floppies o
  CD's (ISO9660, 8+3 only) alon
  with a paper sheet providing
  information about Title,
  Handle, Group, Compo, HW
  requirements and execution
  instructions.
* Compo disks, CD's and video
  tapes will not be returned.
* All entries for Amiga can be
  compressed with either LZX or
  LHA.
* All entries for PC must be
  compressed with ZIP, and read
  for distribution.
* No self-extracting archives
  will be allowed.
* No other archive-types will b
  allowed.
* Contributions with racial
  content (incl. anti-racial),
  and other radical content wil
  not be accepted.
* Contributions must be virus
  free and Y2K compliant.









            [Please Note]

* We will not accept anybody
  selling anything without our
  permission.
* Alcohol and drugs are not
  allowed at the party place. If
  we find any it will be
  confiscated and not given
  back.
* Intoxicated people will be
  thrown out or handed over to
  the police.
* We will not accept weapons,
  spraycans or firework etc.
* People who cause damages of
  any kind will of course have
  to pay for it.
* We take no responsibility for
  illegal swapping, software,
  hardware, video etc.
* Presale tickets from
  Arte/Billetnet available for
  DKK 300, and DKK 350 at the
  door. Additional DKK 50 for
  arrival before opening.














