- Competition Rules

Below the rules for main competitions. 
Forward questions to compo@theparty.dk.

   [Amiga Demo]

* Take up no more
  than 6 MB on
  disk in
  uncompressed
  form.
* Max. one demo
  per coder.
* HD installable
  and runable
* The demo must
  make a clean
  exit to a prompt
* Must work after
  SetPatch is
  installed
* No more than 10
  min. will be
  shown.

        [PC Demo]
* Must be a standalone
  executable with or
  without data files.
* Use no more than 560 
  KB of conventional
  memory.
* Support silent mode 
  (-nosound). 
* Take up no more than 
  6 MB on disk in
  executable form.
* Run while HIMEM.SYS 
  is loaded.
* Max. 
  screenresolution is 
  1024 x 768. 
* Change of screenmode 
  during the demo is
  not recommended.
* Soundblaster AWE 32 
  must be supported,
  but if the demo also 
  supports GUS, it
  will be utilized in
  presentation.
* Max. one demo per
  coder.
* No more than 10 min.
  will be shown. 


[Win98 Demo]  [Cut -ed]

 [WiLD! Classic] 
* In this competition
  there are 
  practically no
  restrictions, except
  that it must be 
  shown by a computer
* Allowed audio
  connectors:
  (mini)jack 
  (mono/stereo),
  scart, phono
  (mono/stereo).
* Allowed video
  connectors: Phono 
  composite pal,
  VGA/SVGA 15 pin SUBD
  (max. 1024 x 768), 
  RGB 23 pin SUBD 
  (Amiga), scart
  composite pal, SVHS
  mini din.
* Note: The computer
  used must have 
  significantly other 
  specs then the compo 
  machines have, and
  not just a CPU 
  running at a higher 
  speed. 
* A complete list of
  the hardware & 
  software used must
  be available.
* No more than 15 min.
  will be shown.




    [Video Demo]
* The only rules in
  this competition,
  is that the video
  must mainly be
  computer
  generated, and
  delivered on a
  video tape.
* Entries must be
  delivered on VHS, 
  SVHS or Betacam
  SP tape.
* A complete list
  of the hardware &
  software used
  must be 
  available.
* No more than 15
  min. will be shown.
 [Java Demo]
* Will be shown in
  latest Netscape
  Navigator release
  version (not beta)
  under WinNT4.0.
* Shown from a web
  server via LAN
* Must be 100% pure
  java applet, ie.
  platform
  independable.
* Max 6MB compiled
  including all class
  and html files,
  graphics and
  soundtracks. A zip
  or jar archive may
  be used.
* No more than 5 min.
  will be shown.
* Source code need not
  to be submitted
* May run in Navigator
  window or separate
  window.
* Html page in which
  to run the applet
  must be provided,
  and max resolution
  is 640x480/24bit.
* Only one demo per
  coder







[Java Intro] 
* Will be shown in
  latest Netscape
  Navigator release
  version (not beta) 
  under WinNT4.0.
* Shown from a web
  server via LAN
* Must be 100% pure
  java applet, ie.
  platform
  independable. 
* Max 100KB compiled 
  including all
  class and html
  files, graphics 
  and soundtracks. A 
  zip or jar archive 
  may be used.
* No more than 5
  min. will be
  shown.
* Source code need 
  not to be 
  submitted 
* Html page in which 
  to run the applet 
  must be provided, 
  and max resolution 
  is 640x480/24bit. 
* Only one demo per 
  coder

[PC Intro]
* Must be a
  standalone
  executable with
  or without data
  files.
* Use no more than
  560 KB of
  conventional
  memory.
* Exit by pressing
  ESC-key at any
  time.
* Support silent
  mode (-nosound).
* Take up no more
  than 64 KB on
  disk in
  executable form.
* Change of
  screenmode
  during the demo
  is not
  recommended.
* Soundblaster AWE
  32 or GUS is
  allowed.
* Run while
  HIMEM.SYS is
  loaded.
* Max. one intro
  per coder.
* No more than 5
  min. will be
  shown. 












    [Amiga Intro]
* Max. size 40 KB. 
* HD installable/runnable 
* The intro must make a
  clean exit to a prompt
* Must work after 
  SetPatch is installed
* Max. one intro per 
  coder.
* Must be right
  mousebutton exitable.
* No more than 5 min.
  will be shown.







    [Pixel Gfx]
* Max. size is 1 MB.
* Max. screenmode
  is 1024 x 768
  pixels.
* Max. screendepth
  is 24 bitplanes.
* Accepted
  filetypes: IFF,
  TIFF, GIF, PCX,
  JPEG, TARGA,
  PNG.
* The picture has
  to be hand
  drawn, and not
  generated or
  calculated.
* Max. one picture
  per graphician.

[Raytraced Gfx]
* Max. size is 1 MB.
* Max. screenmode is 1024 x
  768 pixels.
* Max. screendepth is 24
  bitplanes.
* Accepted filetypes: IFF,
  TIFF, GIF, PCX, JPEG,
  TARGA, PNG.
* The picture has to be
  computer 
  generated/calculated, and
  not pixeled
* Max. one picture per
  graphician.





  [4 Ch. Music]
* Max. size is 1 MB.
* Must be Protracker
  format.
* Will be played
  with Accessible
  Player (Amiga).
* Max. one tune
  per musician.
* Max. 5 min.
  will be played.

[Multi Channel Music]
* Max. size is 1 MB.
* Accepted formats:
  Fast Tracker 2, 
  Impulse Tracker, 
  Scream Tracker 3,
  Octamed. 
* Entries will be 
  played on a GUS 
  Max or Amiga 
  (Octamed). 
* Max. one tune per 
  musician. 
* Max. 5 min. will
  be played. 

[Fast Website]
* You have 4 hours 
  to make a website 
  from scratch,the 
  theme will be
  announced at the 
  start of the
  competition.
* The making of the 
  website will take
  place on a stage.
* Will be shown in
  latest Netscape
  Navigator release
  version (not beta).
* The website max
  size must fit to a
  resolution of
  1024x768/24bit.
* At the end of the
  competition, the
  web site have to
  be delivered on a
  floppy disk(PC
  1.44MB), ready to
  be shown.
* Pathnames must be
  relative.
* The web site may
  not demand use of
  plugins like flash
  and shockwave.
* Java and Java
  Script is allowed.

[Coca Cola Bd Crashing]
* Well the rules are
  quite simple.
* You have to be the
  fastest to drink 1.5L
  CocaCola, without too
  much going on the
  floor, or in the
  bucket :-) 








   [C64 Graphics]
* Must be new gfx, and
  please, no scanning
  or wirring. Use your
  talent!
* Music with the GFX
  will not be played.
* No sprites or moving
  parts in the
  picture!.
* Must be executable. 

[C64 Music] 
* No picture will be 
  shown with the music.
* Must be
  executable. 
* Please specify if 
  new or old Sid
  Chip is used.
   [C64 Demo]
* Standard C-64 
  without
  accessories. 
* Must be executable. 
* Please specify if
  new or old Sid Chip 
  is used.
* Max. length 10 min. 

  [Amiga Hardware]
* For the Amiga Demo
  and Amiga Intro
* Amiga 1200
* 060 50 MHz
* 16 MB FAST ram
* 2 MB CHIP ram
* Note, the Amiga
  productions must
  also work on 030
  50MHz with FPU.

[Java Hardware]

* For the Java Demo,
  Java Intro and
  Fast Website, the
  PC that will be
  used is
* Pentium 233 MHz
  MMX 
* 96MB RAM
* SVGA 32bit
  Truecolor 4MB RAM
 
[PC Hardware]

* The PC used for the
  PC demo, PC Intro
  and Windows 98 Demo
  will be:
* Pentium 233 MHz MMX
* 32 MB RAM
* SVGA 32bit Truecolor 
  4MB RAM 
* SVGA by VESA 1.2
  Support (VESA 2.0
  with SDD/UniVbe)
* Soundblaster AWE 32
  and GUS MAX with 1MB
  RAM.
* For Win98 demo also:
  Voodoo graphics
  adapter (API: OpenGL
  and DirectX v6.0) 